radiographic_examinations.findings: Lungs clear with no pulmonary mass, pleural effusion, or pneumothorax; normal heart size and no pericardial effusion; normal liver, pancreas, spleen, and adrenals; kidneys without hydronephrosis; soft tissue density at the descending colon at the splenic flexure with demonstration of a diverticulum; no pathologic retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy; normal abdominal aorta; normal anteverted uterus; small loculated structure behind the pelvis likely representing small bowel loops; no pelvic free air, free fluid, or pathologic lymphadenopathy; no suspicious osteolytic or osteoblastic lesions.
